✅ PharmaMAS – Complete Requirements List
1️⃣ Core Technologies

These are the main technologies used to build the Multi-Agent System:

✔ Python 3.10+

Primary programming language for the entire project.

✔ CrewAI

Framework for building Multi-Agent AI systems.

✔ LangChain

For LLM-based task execution (if needed, optional).

2️⃣ Python Libraries Used

These are installed inside Google Colab:

AI + Agents

crewai

openai (or any LLM provider mock)

langchain

Data Handling

pandas

json

csv

openpyxl (for Excel)

PDF Generation

reportlab

Environment Management

python-dotenv

Frontend (Optional)

streamlit

cloudflared (for tunneling UI in Colab)

3️⃣ Infrastructure / Runtime Environment
✔ Google Colab Notebook

Used for coding, testing, and running the MAS

Temporary filesystem with /content/

✔ Cloudflared Tunnel

Used to expose Streamlit UI

No password, no login required


4️⃣ Mock Datasets Used

All mock datasets created inside /mock_data/:

✔ 1. IQVIA Market Data (iqvia_mock.json)

Market size

CAGR

Competitor list

Therapy area data

✔ 2. Patent Data (patent_mock.json)

Active and expired patents

Expiry year

Patent title

Status

✔ 3. Clinical Trials Data (clinical_mock.json)

Ongoing trials

Phase

Indication

Sponsor

✔ 4. EXIM API Data (exim_mock.csv)

Export value

Import value

Destination country

Historical data

✔ 5. Web Intelligence Data (web_mock.json)

Scientific articles

Summaries

Publication year

✔ 6. Internal Knowledge Data (simulated text)

Internal insights

Strategy notes

5️⃣ Multi-Agent Components
1. Master Agent

Orchestrates tasks

Coordinates Worker Agents

Synthesizes results

Runs repurposing heuristics

2. Worker Agents

Market Insights Agent

Patent Landscape Agent

Clinical Trials Agent

EXIM Trade Agent

Web Intelligence Agent

Internal Knowledge Agent

3. Report Generator Agent

Creates professional PDF

Creates Excel dashboard

